author: Blust
notes: This list appears to be represent a mixture of the Baikeno, Molo and Amfo'an dialects -ASchAnnotations made on the basis of Owens (2016) by ASch.
classification: Austronesian, Malayo-Polynesian, Central-Eastern, Central Malayo-Polynesian, Timor, Extra-Ramelaic, West

author: to turn
glottocode: Owens (2016) gives the borrowing -bani for this meaning

author: tongue
glottocode: < PCEMP *maya; Loss of CEMP y is regular.

author: wife
glottocode: Shows Amfo'an consonant insertion; regular reflex of PMP *bahi

author: to die, be dead
glottocode: This a compound, with metathesised form. Unmetathesised root is -mate

author: water
glottocode: The final l appears to represent an unetymological element that is regularly appended to vowel final forms in the Baikeno dialect

author: star
glottocode: Owens (2016) gived fkuun for the Molo dialect; he sees this as a regular reflex of PMP *bituqən

author: small
glottocode: Reflects PMP *anak 'child'; Owens (2016) gives root as anaʔ; the form given in this list may be a reduplication.

author: thin
glottocode: Owens (2016) gives mainihas for 'thin', representing a regular reflex of PMP *ma-nipis. The form given in this list appears to represent a rough transcription of the phonemic form of Owens (2016) and so is coded as part of cognate set 1.

author: old
glottocode: This appears to be an affixed form erroneously included here. Owens (2016) gives mnaaʔ 'old' regularly reflecting PMP *daqan meaning 'old (time), long ago'
